<H3> <TI>   Guidance Alignment Building for H-2 Launch Site Detailed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94P60095A Tokyo NASDA NEWS in Japanese Oct 93 pp 8-9 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> 94P60095A </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo NASDA NEWS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:CSO 

  [Text] The Guidance Alignment Building (GAB) is located 
about 100 meters from the Pad Service Tower (PST). A theodolite 
is set up at GAB, which measures azimuth of the airframe at PST. 
<H5>  Main Structure and Function of GAB: </H5>
  1) Architecture: 
  a) Building 
  b) Theodolite foundation 
  c) Basic prism foundation 
  d) Monument foundation 
  2) Electric facilities: 
  a) Panelboard 
  b) Lighting facility 
  c) Broadcasting facility 
  d) General facility 
  e) Air conditioning facility 
  f) Earth terminal board 



  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|GAB Structure                                                              | 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|                  |Structure         |Quantity          |Note              | 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|1: GAB            |                  |                  |                  | 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|Building          |Reinforced concre-|49.6m[.sup]2[/] |                  | 
|                  |te                |                  |                  | 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|Theodolite founda-|``                |1                 |Indoor            | 
|tion              |                  |                  |                  | 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|Basic prism found-|``                |1                 |No. 1 Monument; I-| 
|ation             |                  |                  |ndoor             | 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|2: Monument found-|``                |3                 |Nos. 2, 3, &amp; 4| 
|ation             |                  |                  | Monuments; Outdo-| 
|                  |                  |                  |or                | 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------- 











<H5>  Alignment Measurement </H5>
  The azimuth of the IMU porro optical axis is measured by 
looking at the porro of the Inertial Measuring Unit (IMU) aboard 
the H-2 rocket's second stage by opening the front shutter of 
the GAB and the observation window of the PST. 




